.TH MILSPEC-CONTROL 1 "July 2025" "Dell MIL-SPEC Utilities" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
milspec-control \- Control utility for Dell MIL-SPEC subsystem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B milspec-control
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIARGUMENTS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B milspec-control
is a command-line utility for controlling and configuring Dell military
specification hardware features through the dell-milspec kernel driver.
It provides access to Mode 5 security levels, DSMIL subsystem activation,
and other military-grade features.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Display the current MIL-SPEC system status including Mode 5 level, DSMIL
configuration, security state, and hardware capabilities. This is the
default command if none is specified.
.TP
.B mode5 \fILEVEL\fR
Set the Mode 5 security level (0-4). Higher levels provide increased
security but may restrict system capabilities.
.RS
.TP
.B 0
DISABLED - No Mode 5 protection
.TP
.B 1
STANDARD - Basic protection, VM migration allowed
.TP
.B 2
ENHANCED - VMs locked to hardware
.TP
.B 3
PARANOID - Automatic secure wipe on intrusion
.TP
.B 4
PARANOID_PLUS - Maximum security (IRREVERSIBLE!)
.RE
.TP
.B dsmil \fIMODE\fR
Activate DSMIL (Dell System Military) subsystems in the specified mode (0-3).
.RS
.TP
.B 0
OFF - All subsystems disabled
.TP
.B 1
BASIC - Essential military features only
.TP
.B 2
ENHANCED - Full tactical capabilities
.TP
.B 3
CLASSIFIED - Restricted mode
.RE
.TP
.B activate
Force activation of all MIL-SPEC features. This attempts to enable all
hardware capabilities including Mode 5, DSMIL subsystems, and crypto hardware.
.TP
.B measure
Trigger TPM measurement of the current MIL-SPEC configuration. This records
the system state in TPM PCRs for attestation purposes.
.TP
.B wipe
Initiate emergency data destruction. This command requires explicit
confirmation and will IRREVERSIBLY destroy all data on the system.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-device \fIPATH\fR
Specify the device path (default: /dev/milspec)
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-force
Force dangerous operations without additional confirmation. Required for
setting Mode 5 to PARANOID_PLUS level.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-color
Enable colored output (default if output is a terminal)
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with additional details
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or operation failed
.TP
.B 2
Usage error or invalid arguments
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /dev/milspec
Character device for MIL-SPEC driver communication
.TP
.I /sys/devices/platform/dell-milspec/
Sysfs interface for MIL-SPEC attributes
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show current MIL-SPEC status:
.B milspec-control status
.TP
Set Mode 5 to ENHANCED level:
.B milspec-control mode5 2
.TP
Activate DSMIL in BASIC mode:
.B milspec-control dsmil 1
.TP
Force activation with verbose output:
.B milspec-control -v activate
.TP
Set maximum security (requires force flag):
.B milspec-control -f mode5 4
.SH SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
This utility requires root privileges to operate. Mode 5 PARANOID_PLUS
level is irreversible once activated. The emergency wipe command will
immediately destroy all data without possibility of recovery.
